The pluses: - A great happy hour from 4-6  - Occasionally, you'll get a stellar sale on wine (A co-worker and I got a dry Riesling on sale for $12!
) - Cozy patio - Consistent service - "Hole in the wall" feeling to the place  The negatives: - "Comfort food" isn't usually healthy food - A little pricey for what you get...
If you're in the area, it's definitely a great place to try.
But I wouldn't go out of your way to try it!

