Wally's is my good ole go-to!
It seems that there are very few decent straight up American restaurants in the Biltmore/Arcadia area.
Whenever I'm not sure what I'm in the mood for, or don't want to be bothered with a hustle & bustle type place, Wally's it is!
Don't expect to order healthy here, their menu is more on the side of comfort food, that being said I've never had a bad meal.
The portions are very generous, and the prices are reasonable.
The service here is so welcoming, they treat you as if you've been coming here for years.
They have great sangria and lots of decent beer on tap to go with their delicious food.
My favorite dish so far has been the Prime Rib dip, it's fantastic and full of flavor, and they also have awesome fries (a mix of sweet potato and regular).
This place is totally worth the cheat!
I highly recommend Wally's, as it's a great local restaurant.

